reviews.reviewText: Simple to assemble. Just be careful not to overtighten things. Came protected nicely. Good finishes on the wood and the painted surfaces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute little table
reviews.reviewText: It’s quite cute and went together pretty easily. All pieces were there and needed tools came with it. My only complaint that I took off one star for is that the drawers have to be forced shut. It’s not a huge deal, but I don’t know if it’s how the product was cut or if it’s a malfunction. Again, it’s not the end of the world and over all I’m very satisfied with this item.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My teenage daughter recently used a tiny chainsaw to dismantle a loft bed in her room, so it came as a surprise to us when we struggled to assemble this nightstand, even with the hilarious instructions. I am envious of other reviews that state this was an easy assembly.Once assembled--a process that took us a couple of times, because of the frustration--it is a lovely nightstand. She does have a smaller bedroom and this is a perfect fit for her.The contrast of a black nightstand with a cream-colored drawer is very classy. She is able to tuck many of her smaller needs into the drawer, and the top has been nice to hold a small lamp as well as her phone and other technology needs. The drawer does slide open and closed nicely and is just large enough for one of our cats to snuggle up in when my daughter inevitably leaves the drawer open.It is a very attractive nightstand for the price, and perfect for smaller rooms or guest rooms!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic solution to a feline problem
reviews.reviewText: Disclaimer: We got this from Amazon Vine in exchange for an honest review.This little nightstand is a lifesaver! At least for our cat! :P My husband has been using a big cardboard box as a nightstand since we moved, and one of our cats adores getting on top of it to scratch and play with anything on top. Unfortunately, this led to the top of the box beginning to sag, items disappearing into the void of the box or under the bed, and sodas being straight out of the question unless they were sealed in bottles. Since his meds are one thing that he kept on the box, all of this was highly problematic. We started looking for an affordable solution not long after we moved in, but hadn't found anything really suitable.I was ridiculously excited, therefore, when this item came up on Vine! It was the perfect size and, unlike many of the other items we had looked at, not only does it have a top shelf, but a second, lower shelf, which resists kitty aggression MUCH better and is tall enough to hold a soda can! It also has a drawer, where meds, glasses, and other items that should NOT be accessible to cats (or the random nighttime arm sweep) can live. Sold!We were pleasantly surprised to find that the instructions were not only easy to follow and quite thorough, they were also hilarious! See the photos for some of the best instructions that had us laughing. They were pretty much on the nose that it took about 45 minutes to put together, and could be done by just about anyone.This nightstand is great and well worth the asking price. We are actually pondering getting a second to upgrade me from using a 3-drawer plastic tote, lol.
